ated to the add method?]\n","     */\n","    public int multiply(int a, int b) {\n","        return a * b;\n","    }\n","\n","    /**\n","     * Subtracts two integers.\n","     *\n","     * @deprecated Use {@link #add(int, int)} with negative values instead.\n","     * @ [Fill in]\n","     * @ [Fill in]\n","     * @ [Fill in]\n","     */ [Fill in]\n","    @Deprecated\n","    public int subtract(int a, int b) {\n","        return a - b;\n","    }\n","\n","    /**\n","     * Main method for testing the utility methods.\n","     *\n","     * @param args command-line arguments\n","     */\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        MathUtils mathUtils = new MathUtils();\n","\n","        int sum = mathUtils.add(5, 10);\n","        System.out.println(\"Sum: \" + sum);\n","\n","        try {\n","            double division = mathUtils.divide(10, 2);\n","            System.out.println(\"Division: \" + division);\n","        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {\n","            System.err.println(e.getMessage());\n","        }\n","\n","        int product = mathUtils.multiply(5, 3);\n","        System.out.println(\"Product: \" + product);\n","\n","        int difference = mathUtils.subtract(10, 5);\n","        System.out.println(\"Difference (Deprecated): \" + difference);\n","    }\n","}"],"metadata":{"id":"kLT3jHyvlIl6"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Compare yours to the example that I have filled in:"],"metadata":{"id":"wwy1jovwnBn_"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["!wget -qO- https://tylerchan.me/temp/JavadocExerciseFilled.java | tr -d '\\r' > JavadocExerciseFilled.java\n","!colordiff JavadocExercise.java JavadocExerciseFilled.java -y"],"metadata":{"id":"v3VP_cyYoEM4"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","# **7. Syntax, Logical, and Runtime Errors in Java**\n","\n","- **Syntax Errors**: The Java compiler (`javac`) will detect these (e.g., missing semicolons, typos in keywords).\n","- **Logical Errors**: The code compiles and runs but doesn’t do what you intend (e.g., using `<=` instead of `<`).\n","- **Runtime Errors**: Errors that occur during execution (e.g., `NullPointerException`).\n","\n","We’ll demonstrate a quick snippet below with a deliberate runtime error and see how java responds."],"metadata":{"id":"pOwS0hvcx9Ap"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile RuntimeErrorExample.java\n","public class RuntimeErrorExample {\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        int a = 5;\n","        int b = 0;\n","\n","        // Runtime error: Division by zero\n","        int result = a / b; // This will throw ArithmeticException\n","        System.out.println(\"Result: \" + result);\n","    }\n","}"],"metadata":{"id":"WuGzdUuBt1Zy"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["!javac RuntimeErrorExample.java\n","!java RuntimeErrorExample"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"FxziDAH5t-yy","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1737432219620,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":1452,"user":{"displayName":"Tyler","userId":"06315977947093285888"}},"outputId":"23dbf168-d2bc-4d76-8de3-adfc66da7ad9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Exception in thread \"main\" java.lang.ArithmeticException: / by zero\n","\tat RuntimeErrorExample.main(RuntimeErrorExample.java:7)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","**Exercise**:  \n","- Fix the syntax error of the exercise below, then compile again successfully."],"metadata":{"id":"ACuuJdu3uKH2"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile SyntaxErrorExample.java\n","public class SyntaxErrorExample {\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        System.out.println(\"Hello, world!);\n","    }\n","}\n"],"metadata":{"id":"eYbsFybouHGF"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["!javac SyntaxErrorExample.java"],"metadata":{"id":"Uay5JzAWuVIl"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","# **8. Java Exceptions**\n","\n","Java uses exceptions to handle runtime errors. We typically use `try`/`catch` blocks to manage them.\n","\n","```java\n","try {\n","    // Risky code here\n","} catch (Exception e) {\n","    // Handle exception\n","}\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","**Exercise**\n","1. Add a try-catch block to the exercise below to handle it by displaying a user-friendly error message.\n","2. Then, ensure the program continues executing other operations after handling the exception."],"metadata":{"id":"5O9dDFuVuUWF"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile ArithmeticExceptionExample.java\n","/**\n"," * A program to demonstrate deliberate throwing and handling of ArithmeticException.\n"," */\n","public class ArithmeticExceptionExample {\n","\n","    /**\n","     * Divides two numbers and handles ArithmeticException if division by zero occurs.\n","     *\n","     * @param a the numerator\n","     * @param b the denominator\n","     */\n","    public static void divideNumbers(int a, int b) {\n","          System.out.println(\"Attempting to divide \" + a + \" by \" + b + \"...\");\n","          int result = a / b; // This will throw ArithmeticException if b is 0\n","          System.out.println(\"Result: \" + result);\n","    }\n","\n","    /**\n","     * Main method to execute the program.\n","     *\n","     * @param args command-line arguments\n","     */\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        // Deliberately passing zero as the denominator to trigger the exception\n","        divideNumbers(10, 0);\n","\n","        // Program continues executing other tasks\n","        System.out.println(\"Continuing program execution...\");\n","    }\n","}"],"metadata":{"id":"d-cvqXhvvOP8"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Compile and run the program\n","!javac ArithmeticExceptionExample.java\n","!java ArithmeticExceptionExa