ss CalculatorTest {\n","\n","    @Test\n","    public void testAdd() {\n","        Calculator calc = new Calculator();\n","        // We expect 3 + 5 = 8\n","        assertEquals(8, calc.add(3, 5));\n","    }\n","}"],"metadata":{"id":"13EAq-M_Bn5c"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Compile Java source files.\n","# Note: We only need the .class files to compile test code, no external JAR required at compile-time\n","# because JUnit 5 annotations (Test, Assertions, etc.) are source-level,\n","# but to be safe, we include the console JAR on the classpath so the references resolve.\n","!javac -cp .:junit-platform-console-standalone-1.9.3.jar com/mypackage/Calculator.java com/testpackage/CalculatorTest.java\n","!java -jar junit-platform-console-standalone-1.9.3.jar \\\n","    --class-path . \\\n","    --scan-class-path"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"NE7GyHVfrFFx","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1737432299776,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":3700,"user":{"displayName":"Tyler","userId":"06315977947093285888"}},"outputId":"3cf7f558-d508-4fda-dfd5-0c836f63d61d"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Thanks for using JUnit! Support its development at https://junit.org/sponsoring\n","\n","\u001b[36m╷\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[36m├─\u001b[0m \u001b[36mJUnit Jupiter\u001b[0m \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[36m├─\u001b[0m \u001b[36mJUnit Vintage\u001b[0m \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[36m│  └─\u001b[0m \u001b[36mCalculatorTest\u001b[0m \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[36m│     └─\u001b[0m \u001b[31mtestAdd\u001b[0m \u001b[31m✘\u001b[0m \u001b[31mexpected:<8> but was:<0>\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[36m└─\u001b[0m \u001b[36mJUnit Platform Suite\u001b[0m \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m\n","\n","Failures (1):\n","  JUnit Vintage:CalculatorTest:testAdd\n","    MethodSource [className = 'com.testpackage.CalculatorTest', methodName = 'testAdd', methodParameterTypes = '']\n","    => java.lang.AssertionError: expected:<8> but was:<0>\n","       org.junit.Assert.fail(Assert.java:89)\n","       org.junit.Assert.failNotEquals(Assert.java:835)\n","       org.junit.Assert.assertEquals(Assert.java:647)\n","       org.junit.Assert.assertEquals(Assert.java:633)\n","       com.testpackage.CalculatorTest.testAdd(CalculatorTest.java:13)\n","       java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.DirectMethodHandleAccessor.invoke(DirectMethodHandleAccessor.java:103)\n","       java.base/java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:580)\n","       org.junit.runners.model.FrameworkMethod$1.runReflectiveCall(FrameworkMethod.java:59)\n","       org.junit.internal.runners.model.ReflectiveCallable.run(ReflectiveCallable.java:12)\n","       org.junit.runners.model.FrameworkMethod.invokeExplosively(FrameworkMethod.java:56)\n","       [...]\n","\n","Test run finished after 83 ms\n","[         4 containers found      ]\n","[         0 containers skipped    ]\n","[         4 containers started    ]\n","[         0 containers aborted    ]\n","[         4 containers successful ]\n","[         0 containers failed     ]\n","[         1 tests found           ]\n","[         0 tests skipped         ]\n","[         1 tests started         ]\n","[         0 tests aborted         ]\n","[         0 tests successful      ]\n","[         1 tests failed          ]\n","\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","**Exercise**:\n","1. Fix the `add()` method to return the correct result.\n","2. Recompile and run the tests again to ensure they pass.\n","\n","---"],"metadata":{"id":"hJUX1aUhu3n7"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **10. `assert` vs. `assert*()` in JUnit**\n","\n","- **Java `assert`**: A language feature used for internal invariants. Disabled by default. Enable with `-ea` or `-enableassertions`.\n","- **JUnit `assertSomething()`** methods: Testing methods (e.g., `assertEquals`, `assertTrue`, etc.) that are always executed (unless you specifically skip tests).\n","\n","---"],"metadata":{"id":"YWBe-FsnxyPe"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","## 10.1 Example of Java assertions\n","Java assertions (assert) are a built-in language feature used to verify that certain conditions hold true at specific points in your program. They are primarily intended for debugging and development purposes to check for internal invariants or assumptions. Java assertions can be enabled or disabled at runtime with `-ea`.\n","\n","```java\n","assert x > 0 : \"x should be positive!\";\n","```\n","### To enable this in Eclipse:"],"metadata":{"id":"N2dNwrbD92WB"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["![eclipse_assert1.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"BaoSJcAy1Kpj"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["![eclipse_assert2.png](data:image/png;base64,)"],"metadata":{"id":"yH4myEBh1tIw"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","## 10.2 Example of JUnit assertions\n","JUnit assertions (`assertSomething()` methods) are part of the JUnit testing framework, used for writing and executing unit tests. They check whether actual values match expected values during test execution.\n","\n","Examples of Common JUnit Assertions:\n","- `assertEquals(expected, actual)`: Checks if expected equals actual.\n","- `assertTrue(condition)`: Checks if the condition is true.\n","- `assertNull(object)`: Checks if the object is null.\n","- `assertThrows(Exception.class, executable)`: Checks if the executable throws the specified exception.\n","---"],"metadata":{"id":"lR_NlTtR1JOS"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 10.3 When to Use Which?\n","Java assert:\n","- For lightweight debugging checks during development.\n","- When you want checks that can be turned off in production.\n","- Example: Checking algorithm invariants or state assumptions during development.\n","\n","JUnit Assertions:\n","- For verifying code correctness in unit tests.\n","- When writing tests to confirm expected outputs and behavior.\n","- Example: Ensuring that your methods produce the expected results or handle edge cases properly.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**Exercise**\n","1. Make the following code fail an assertion before the print statement.\n","2. Edit the run command to enable assertions."],"metadata":{"id":"k3ng15nd-CWn"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile AssertionExample.java\n","public class AssertionExample {\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        // assert something\n","        System.out.println(\"This line won't execute if assertion fails.\");\n","    }\n","}"],"metadata":{"id":"84xP79Fpu22m"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["!javac AssertionExample.java\n","!java AssertionExample"],"metadata":{"id":"fQyCt6eqzlhQ"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","# **11. Public and Other Access Modifiers**\n","\n","Java has four levels of access control:\n","\n","1. `public`\n","2. `protected`\n","3. *(default)* (i.e., no modifier)\n","4. `private`\n","\n","**Fields, methods, and classes** each behave differently with these modifiers. Refer to:  \n","[https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/accesscontrol.html](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/accesscontrol.html)\n","\n","**Examples**:\n","\n","```java\n","public class Example {\n","    private int privateField;\n","    protected int protectedField;\n","    int defaultField; // package-private (default)\n","    public int publicField;\n","\n","    private void privateMethod() { }\n","    protected void protectedMethod() { }\n","    void defaultMethod() { }\n","    public void publicMethod() { }\n","}\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","**Exercise**\n","1. Uncomment some lines in the files below to see javac show you errors when accessing fields the package doesn't have access too."],"metadata":{"id":"yNlB8UxE1zzO"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile Person.java\n","package com.example.accessmodifiers;\n","\n","/**\n"," * A class demonstrating different access modifiers.\n"," */\n","public class Person {\n","\n","    // Access Modifiers\n","    public String name = \"John\";          // Public: Accessible anywhere\n","    private int age = 30;                 // Private: Accessible only within this class\n","    protected String address = \"Earth\";  // Protected: Accessible within the package and subclasses\n","    String email = \"john@example.com\";   // Package-private: Accessible only within the same package\n","}\n"],"metadata":{"id":"JgEJYXNn2ba4"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile Main.java\n","package com.example.accessmodifiers;\n","\n","/**\n"," * A class to test the accessibility of members from the Person class.\n"," */\n","public class Main {\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        Person person = new Person();\n","\n","        // Public field: Accessible\n","        System.out.println(\"Name (public): \" + person.name);\n","\n","        // Private field: Not accessible directly\n","        // System.out.println(\"Age (private): \" + person.age); // Uncomment to see the error\n","\n","        // Protected field: Accessible because we are in the same package\n","        System.out.println(\"Address (protected): \" + person.address);\n","\n","        // Package-private field: Accessible because we are in the same package\n","        System.out.println(\"Email (package-private): \" + person.email);\n","    }\n","}\n"],"metadata":{"id":"ivLGA6af2iqF"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["%%writefile AnotherClass.java\n","package com.example.anotherpackage;\n","\n","import com.example.accessmodifiers.Person;\n","\n","/**\n"," * A class to test accessibility from a different package.\n"," */\n","public class AnotherClass {\n","    public static void main(String[] args) {\n","        Person person = new Person();\n","\n","        // Public field: Accessible\n","        System.out.println(\"Name (public): \" + person.name);\n","\n","        // Private field: Not accessible directly\n","        // System.out.println(\"Age (private): \" + person.age); // Uncomment to see the error\n","\n","        // Protected field: Not accessible because we are not in the same package or a subclass\n","        // System.out.println(\"Address (protected): \" + person.address); // Uncomment to see the error\n","\n","        // Package-private field: Not accessible because we are not in the same package\n","        // System.out.println(\"Email (package-private): \" + person.email); // Uncomment to see the error\n","    }\n","}\n"],"metadata":{"id":"FDfygs5H2psu"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["!rm -rf com\n","!javac -d . AnotherClass.java Person.java Main.java\n","!java com.example.accessmodifiers.Main\n","!java com.example.anotherpackage.AnotherClass"],"metadata":{"id":"unWjqPE812zf"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}